==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic, related to [[agen|āgen]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'a:gnian/

===Verb===
'''āgnian''' (class 2 weak)
# to claim possession
# to take possession, to [[appropriate]]
#:''Hu miht ðu, ðonne, ðe agnian heora god?''  How then can you appropriate their good to yourself? (Alfred’s ''de Consolatione Philosophae'')
# to [[possess]]


